**`BpmnNodeHandles`** — renders `@xyflow/react` `<Handle>` components. All handles styled: `h-2 w-2 border border-border bg-card`. Props: `left`, `right` (default true), `top`, `bottom` (default false).

**`BpmnNodeLabel`** — renders: `<p className="select-none text-xs text-foreground ...">`.

**`getNodeLabel(data, fallback)`** — reads `data.label` string, falls back to provided string.

---

## Summary: How Selection Styling Works

1. **`ring-2 ring-ring/40`** is applied via `getBpmnNodeClassName(kind, selected)` to the inner `div` when `selected === true`. This is the primary "selected" indicator — a semi-transparent ring.
2. **`BpmnResizableNode`** additionally shows `<NodeResizer>` (react-flow's built-in resize overlay) and the `bottom-right` resize control handle when selected.
3. Event nodes (`EventShell`) do NOT use `getBpmnNodeClassName` — they don't get the `ring-*` class. Their selection is only indicated by the `<NodeResizer>` appearing.
4. `BpmnLaneNode` does NOT use `BpmnResizableNode` — it has no resize controls and uses `getBpmnNodeClassName('lane', selected)` but only within a plain `div`.

**The selection ring CSS:** `ring-2 ring-ring/40` — Tailwind's `ring` utility using the `--ring` CSS variable at 40% opacity. This is the ONLY selected-state visual diff for most nodes.

